maludb (0.95.0-1) noble; urgency=medium

  * v4.3.0 release. Extension default_version 0.95.0;
    89/89 pg_regress on PostgreSQL 17.
  * Semantic spine (0.95.0): subjects/verbs/edges become the vector
    layer — deterministic in-DB entity cards + trigger-fed dirty
    queue + external embed worker landing in the object-embedding
    rail; materialized similar_to traversal jumps (opt-in via
    rel_filter); unified edge view gains the ingested subject
    relationships (gap fix); statement source_spans[] accretion.
    Chunk-compartment rail frozen/deprecated; extraction JSON
    contract unchanged.
  * Episodes as subjects (0.94.0): every episode is a typed event
    subject with the temporal body as a sidecar; BREAKING ingest
    contract (episodes[] removed — events are subjects[] entries
    with occurred_at).
  * New `maludb` metapackage: the `apt install maludb` entry point,
    depending on postgresql-17-maludb-core (PostgreSQL 17 + pgvector
    + pgaudit + pg_partman via dependencies) and recommending
    maludb-mc2dbd. Refreshed the postgresql-17-maludb-core package
    description (was stuck at the 0.40.0 feature list); declare the
    intentionally-unshipped staged mc2dbd unit in debian/not-installed
    so dh_missing passes. The metapackage also ships the four
    numbered end-to-end SQL example scenarios under
    /usr/share/maludb/examples/, so the README Quickstart's
    `apt install maludb` → `cd /usr/share/maludb` flow is
    self-contained (the version-pinned mist-e2e harness stays
    source-only).

 -- Edward Honour <ed@maludb.org>  Sun, 07 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000

